title: Grateful Dead Live at Madison Square Garden on 1993-09-16
lineage: Set 1: CD -> Samplitude Professional v10.1 -> FLAC
description:
Set 1

Rain, Shakedown Street, Wang Dang Doodle, Cold Rain & Snow, Queen Jane Approximately, Althea, Eternity, Don't Ease Me In

Set 2

China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider, Estimated Prophet-> Eyes Of The World-> Drums-> Space-> Way To Go Home-> The Days Between-> Throwing Stones-> Not Fade Away, E: Liberty

reviews.review_text:
Fifteenth Days Between 15/41: Eyes (10:20)->Drumz (26:53)->WTGH (6:28)->Days Between (9:53)->Throwing Stones->NFA

Opening of a six-night run at MSG. While it doesn't necessarily look it, I really love this first set. Rain opener, then Shakedown. Cold Rain & Snow, even the Queen Jane is beautifully played ("magic wind"), as well as the Althea. Eternity is excellent. Greatest hits second set interspersed with a couple new tunes: Way To Go Home and Days.
